Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.05,0:12:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(972,840)}The path to that SuuAnKou was narrow and treacherous
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.35,0:12:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,HOWEVER
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.00,0:12:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,at the very end of that path
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.30,0:12:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,was a way to flip the game
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.60,0:14:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The east as the flow..
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.58,0:14:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,don't they
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.00,0:14:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, now. it's still okay
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.45,0:14:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi and Hiroyuki are only just BARELY in the game
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.00,0:14:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,With one hit and we can kick them...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.80,0:14:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,YOU MORON(kansai dialect)!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.30,0:14:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What is this fucking mealy mouthed SHIT!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.35,0:14:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Understand what that win means!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.40,0:14:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,They put it all on the line
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.80,0:14:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's got NOTHING to do with their fucking POINTS!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.98,0:14:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Soga,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.98,0:14:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I've already decided what we have to do
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.80,0:14:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.45,0:14:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,As you like
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.60,0:15:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,More and more this looks like the last round, doesn't it
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.50,0:15:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten's SuuAnKou just now
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.85,0:15:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It lit a fire under those fag's asses
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.20,0:15:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,They gonna come at us with everything they got
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.65,0:15:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't a reasonable contest any more
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.55,0:15:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Eat? Or be eaten?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.75,0:15:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a battle of base instinct
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.40,0:15:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.85,0:15:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Abandon yourself entirely to it
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.60,0:15:41.78,small - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1674.667,793.333)}10th Game\NSouth Round 1
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.20,0:16:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Riichi
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.01,0:16:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's come
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.55,0:16:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The first Riichi of the round
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.30,0:16:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Is a Mangan hand
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.85,0:16:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,If he draws his tile, it's over
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.98,0:16:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,My making a quick hand is best here
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.65,0:16:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,but this hand's a slow one as well
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.30,0:16:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,This game doesn't have a "no tenpai penalty"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.20,0:16:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So I just have to not deal into his hand
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.55,0:17:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,SHIT
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.50,0:17:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't an Itsuu
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.80,0:17:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,An end wait on 7 Sou?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.15,0:17:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Why on earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.58,0:17:38.15,small - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1656,792)}10th Game\NSouth Round 3
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.15,0:17:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.01,0:17:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm in Tenpai
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.85,0:17:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,If I discard the 5 Pin it's a 1/4 Pin wait
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.20,0:17:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Or if I discard the 3 Pin it's a 2 Pin/White dragon triple wait
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.05,0:17:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever I do my two White Dragons are dora, plus an Iipeikou
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.35,0:17:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and If I Riichi it's certainly more than Mangan
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.40,0:18:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,There's already two White Dragons discarded...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.95,0:18:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,so my decision is straightforward
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.55,0:18:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Riichi
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.85,0:18:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,With such a readable wait
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.55,0:18:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't be able to get a direct hit
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.75,0:18:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Naturally the West team won't deal into it
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.15,0:18:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But I wasn't expecting that from the start
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.50,0:18:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I WILL DRAW IT
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.85,0:18:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,IT CAN'T BE!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.80,0:18:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,FIVE white dragon tiles???
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.20,0:20:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,FIVE whites?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.28,0:20:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the west team
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.78,0:20:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The West team mixed in an extra White from the start
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.60,0:20:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But... for what purpose?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.90,0:20:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it insurance?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.35,0:20:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're at a disadvantage, just announcing there's 5 white tiles,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.70,0:20:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,will invalidate the round
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.98,0:20:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to be kidding
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.98,0:20:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no reason why I have to play along with this
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.48,0:20:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,BUT, why should I throw away my advantage?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.35,0:20:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,If I complete my hand, I win
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.95,0:20:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,If I draw it I WIN
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.50,0:21:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,South and North wind tiles?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.80,0:21:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I can understand him playing around my Riichi
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.85,0:21:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,but having a North and South wind floating in your hand so late in the game is unusual
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.25,0:21:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,A Kokusi Musou?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.85,0:21:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, more and more it's looking that way
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.25,0:21:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, it is amusing
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.65,0:21:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He may be in tenpai but I can't lose if he's waiting on a White Dragon that will never come
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.60,0:21:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got the other two he's waiting for
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.05,0:21:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if Harada thinks there's two remaining
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.05,0:21:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just impossible for him to get one
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.45,0:21:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And if it's impossible, the chances he deals into my hand increases
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.80,0:22:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,More and more this White Dragon
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.70,0:22:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,looks like a poison mixed in to benefit Harada
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.65,0:22:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and ironically that poison
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.40,0:22:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,is now running through Harada's own veins
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.40,0:22:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Any moment now...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.60,0:22:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,A SIXTH WHITE DRAGON???
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.41,0:22:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,YOU HAVE GOT TO BE FUCKING KIDDING
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.41,0:22:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Enough with the fucking cheating already
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.55,0:22:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Whats the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.05,0:23:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,If it doesn't complete your hand get rid of it, or else...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.95,0:23:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,have you forgotten how to discard?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.45,0:23:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,OH, a White Dragon?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.15,0:23:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.20,0:23:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.85,0:23:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Kokusi Musou
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.55,0:23:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,HA HA HA HA HA!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.00,0:23:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And with that, the game is over!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.05,0:23:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop fucking around,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.50,0:23:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not going to accept a game like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.00,0:23:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,LOOK!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.70,0:23:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What I discarded was the SIXTH White Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.70,0:23:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,A mess like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.45,0:23:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You think I'd let an illegal move like this go through!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.01,0:24:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Illegal?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.01,0:24:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But you yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.65,0:24:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't you already accept that Illegal move?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.28,0:24:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,If you've got two Whites in your hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.30,0:24:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You drew the 5th White right after declaring Riichi
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.20,0:24:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus at that time,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.70,0:24:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You should have noticed something off with the game
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.55,0:24:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you say anything {\b1\i1}then{\b0\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.25,0:24:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, when it suits your purposes...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.40,0:24:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,you accept what's illegal
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.85,0:24:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,but when it's not to your advantage you go around screaming "illegal, illegal!"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.45,0:24:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, that kind of play is simply not acceptable
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.70,0:24:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.15,0:24:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you think so, Akagi?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.25,0:24:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly, it's as you say
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.25,0:24:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,A-Akagi :-(
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.25,0:24:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But Harada,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.25,0:25:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite that, I'm quite sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.25,0:25:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,you haven't won
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.70,0:25:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.50,0:25:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,If you accept there are 6 White Dragon tiles
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.90,0:25:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Naturally this game is an exception
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.30,0:25:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you accept that exception
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.70,0:25:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll have to accept my exception from the rules as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.21,0:25:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.90,0:25:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Head Bump
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.90,0:25:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Head bump?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.45,0:25:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,ha ha ha.\NARE YOU FUKKIN RETARDED?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.00,0:25:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The kid discarded a WHITE DRAGON
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.30,0:25:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You're waiting on a 2/5 Sou (bamboo) or a 5 Pin (dots)
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.15,0:25:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, {\b1\i1}on the surface{\b0\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.01,0:25:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,HUNH?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.31,0:25:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,If there's 6 White Dragons...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.65,0:25:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That means there were tiles left out of the game
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.80,0:25:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably three tiles of two types
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.05,0:25:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I say that White that Hiroyuki discarded isn't a White at all
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.15,0:25:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I say it was destined to be a missing tile I could declare Ron on
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.78,0:25:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Missing tile?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.95,0:25:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.60,0:26:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That tile is precisely
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.25,0:26:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,a 5 Sou (5 bamboo)
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.75,0:26:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,If you examine the left over tiles in that Mahjong case
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.05,0:26:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll soon know if it's among the few left over tiles...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.25,0:26:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,if there's a 5 Sou among them...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.85,0:26:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll accept my head bump
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.70,0:26:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and as it's merely a Tanyao hand
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.20,0:26:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the game will simply continue
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.91,0:26:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But if there isn't a 5 Sou in that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.80,0:26:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You're out of bounds
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.80,0:26:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and the point penalty KNOCKS YOU THE FUCK OUT!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.40,0:26:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,If you agree to that...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.50,0:26:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll accept the bet
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.41,0:26:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,No problem
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.25,0:26:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(972,836)}Akagi,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.25,0:26:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,816)}Please. Don't do it
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.75,0:26:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(972,860)}The tiles the West team swapped
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.50,0:26:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(956,860)}Only two types of tiles out of 34 in Mahjong
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.85,0:26:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(956,828)}Choosing just the 5 sou is not a gyamburu you're likely to win!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.30,0:26:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(980,848)}I'm the one that dealt into Harada's hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.80,0:27:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(956,852)}Hiro,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.80,0:27:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(952,856)}It's gone too far already
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.10,0:27:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(956,828)}Hunh?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.05,0:27:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(972,852)}I declared a Ron
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.50,0:27:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(968,892)}There's no turning back
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.25,0:27:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(976,840)}Whether or not your White should have been a 5 Sou...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.15,0:27:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(976,816)}Is the question at hand
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.91,0:27:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,808)}BUT
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.60,0:27:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(956,800)}Hiroyuki,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.45,0:27:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(976,760)}Akagi Shigeru himself has said as much
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.50,0:27:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(980,780)}There's no taking it back
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.45,0:27:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(972,840)}We can only watch now
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.30,0:27:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi has survived!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.35,0:27:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What i'm afraid of is {\b1\i1}who I am{\b0\i0} dying
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.30,0:27:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't avert your eyes from anything real
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.90,0:27:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The way forward opens!
